<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-456-762  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 456 762.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  August 1989 v14 n8 p82(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Logitech brings finesse to low-cost desktop publishing. (SoftwareReview) (Logitech Finesse computer graphics software) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barker, D.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Logitech Inc's $199 Finesse is a powerful low-enddesktop-publishing package designed to run under DigitalResearch's GEM graphics environment.andP;  Finesse uses a 'text frame'technique in which the user must draw boxes on the screen beforelaying down text.andP;  The program works with many popularword-processor file formats as well as ASCII text, and with TIFF,PCX, Metafile, or bit-mapped graphics.andP;  It handles importation ofgraphic images via the same fill-a-frame procedure used for text.andO;A 'chaining' tool lets the user move text from one frame toanother, and several handy shortcuts speed up text manipulation.andO;Finesse's limitations include the fact that the user can only workon part of a page at a time and slow screen redrawing.andP;  It runs onan IBM PC or compatible with 640 Kbytes of RAM, a hard disk, DOS2.1 or higher, and a CGA, EGA, VGA, or Hercules graphics adapter.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Research Inc. (products)Logitech Inc. (products).andO;Product:   GEM (Computer graphics software) (equipment and supplies)Finesse (Desktop publishing software).andO;Topic:     Desktop publishingEvaluationGraphics SoftwareSoftware SelectionSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>